<i>♪ It's gonna be a bright ♪</i>

837
00:54:46.609 --> 00:54:49.479
<i>♪ Bright sunshiny day ♪</i>

838
00:54:53.248 --> 00:54:58.606
<i>♪ Look all around
Nothing but blue skies ♪</i>

839
00:55:00.568 --> 00:55:05.958
<i>♪ Look straight ahead
Nothing but blue skies ♪</i>

840
00:55:15.327 --> 00:55:16.920
<i>♪ Whoa ♪</i>

841
00:55:17.007 --> 00:55:21.525
<i>♪ I can see clearly now
The rain is gone ♪</i>

842
00:55:24.486 --> 00:55:28.284
<i>♪ I can see all obstacles in my way ♪</i>

843
00:55:28.366 --> 00:55:31.204
All right, everybody.
I want all teams in place,

844
00:55:31.286 --> 00:55:34.844
fully prepared, ready to seal the doors
here and here.

845
00:55:36.206 --> 00:55:39.022
<i>Make certain the digging crew
stays on schedule for breakthrough</i>

846
00:55:39.045 --> 00:55:40.682
<i>midway in the dedication ceremony.</i>

847
00:55:42.126 --> 00:55:44.559
<i>Now all we need is the princess.</i>

848
00:55:58.804 --> 00:56:00.561
Mm.

849
00:56:11.884 --> 00:56:15.594
- This stuff tastes like crap.
- Really? Let me try some.

850
00:56:17.483 --> 00:56:20.518
Hey, it is crap. Not bad.

851
00:56:21.763 --> 00:56:25.801
- Somebody needs to feed that fire.
- Dude, I did it last time.

852
00:56:25.883 --> 00:56:28.601
I'm not gonna get it. It's not my job.

853
00:56:28.843 --> 00:56:30.753
Well, what about the new guy?

854
00:56:30.843 --> 00:56:32.677
He hasn't contributed yet.

855
00:56:33.403 --> 00:56:36.916
And... you know,
he just died in my arms like that.

856
00:56:37.003 --> 00:56:43.113
I... You know, I don't think he ever once
in his life made his own choice.

857
00:56:44.762 --> 00:56:46.311
I never knew it was like that.

858
00:56:47.562 --> 00:56:49.112
I mean, up in the palace...

859
00:56:49.961 --> 00:56:53.639
Well, I guess we just let the General
make all the decisions.

860
00:56:56.041 --> 00:56:57.275
Let me ask you something.

861
00:56:58.161 --> 00:57:00.114
What made you come to the bar that night?

862
00:57:01.440 --> 00:57:03.634
I guess I was looking for
a little trouble.

863
00:57:03.721 --> 00:57:06.198
Well, trouble's my middle name.

864
00:57:06.800 --> 00:57:09.310
Actually, my middle name is Marion, but...

865
00:57:10.120 --> 00:57:12.914
- I don't want you to spread that around.
- You're pretty strange.

866
00:57:13.000 --> 00:57:14.670
You do know that, don't you?

867
00:57:14.760 --> 00:57:18.197
Well, "strange" is not exactly
the word I would use.

868
00:57:18.280 --> 00:57:21.150
- You know, I...
- I like it. You're not like anyone else.

869
00:57:22.200 --> 00:57:25.910
Actually, now that you mention it,
there is a certain strangeness to me.

870
00:57:25.999 --> 00:57:28.793
I mean, it's a, you know,
kind of a bizarre quality.

871
00:57:28.879 --> 00:57:30.789
Some have said "freak."

872
00:57:30.879 --> 00:57:33.356
But it's, uh, you know, complimentary.

873
00:57:37.839 --> 00:57:40.589
Hey, new guy! We need more wood!

874
00:57:43.079 --> 00:57:45.992
I'll be right back.
Just hold that thought.

875
00:57:46.078 --> 00:57:47.955
Whatever it is you were thinking.

876
00:57:49.438 --> 00:57:52.035
Hey, you ever wonder why
they call you guys "pests"?

877
00:57:53.478 --> 00:57:56.675
What if, like,
we're just these tiny little things,

878
00:57:56.758 --> 00:58:01.756
and we're just, like, part of this whole
other huge universe that's, like,

879
00:58:01.837 --> 00:58:04.314
so big we don't even know it exists?

880
00:58:04.757 --> 00:58:07.987
Man, that is so deep.

881
00:58:08.397 --> 00:58:09.194
Perfect!

882
00:58:09.277 --> 00:58:13.075
Nothing like a little manual labor
on the most romantic night of my life.

883
00:58:18.796 --> 00:58:19.755
Hi.

884
00:58:19.997 --> 00:58:22.747
I was in the neighborhood,
and I thought I'd drop in.

885
00:58:24.117 --> 00:58:27.674
This is, uh... very bohemian.

886
00:58:27.996 --> 00:58:31.466
Aloha, dude. Welcome to Insec...

887
00:58:31.555 --> 00:58:32.514
...topia.

888
00:58:32.876 --> 00:58:34.906
Sorry for interrupting.

889
00:58:36.675 --> 00:58:40.909
You see, our princess
has, uh, gone missing,

890
00:58:40.996 --> 00:58:43.069
and we're just sick about it.

891
00:58:44.675 --> 00:58:48.353
She's about yea tall,
fairly easy on the eyes.

892
00:58:49.275 --> 00:58:52.068
- Anybody seen her?
- There she is. That's her. Yeah.

893
00:58:53.555 --> 00:58:56.829
Don't worry, Princess,
you'll be back home soon.

894
00:58:57.394 --> 00:59:00.145
Listen, Cutter, I'm... I'm not going back.

895
00:59:00.634 --> 00:59:03.668
The thing is,
Princess, I got orders.

896
00:59:04.034 --> 00:59:04.993
Orders?

897
00:59:05.153 --> 00:59:07.784
Can't you just once think for yourself?

898
00:59:09.314 --> 00:59:11.628
Well, that was very impressive.

899
00:59:12.074 --> 00:59:13.264
Where's Z?

900
00:59:13.953 --> 00:59:16.190
- Z? He's, uh...
- Dead!

901
00:59:17.553 --> 00:59:18.667
Z's dead.

902
00:59:19.513 --> 00:59:21.030
You don't need to worry about him.

903
00:59:21.113 --> 00:59:25.511
Z's dead. Well, he was an ant with ideas.

904
00:59:26.152 --> 00:59:27.310
Too bad for him.

905
00:59:28.153 --> 00:59:30.510
Princess, your colony needs you.

906
00:59:31.072 --> 00:59:32.666
Cutter!

907
00:59:32.752 --> 00:59:35.666
- Stop right now! Let go of me!
- Bala!

908
00:59:35.992 --> 00:59:37.062
Stop, you... Hey!

909
00:59:38.152 --> 00:59:39.111
Oh, no.

910
00:59:40.272 --> 00:59:41.505
What am I gonna do?

911
00:59:42.272 --> 00:59:45.185
All right, look, look.
Let's be rational about this.

912
00:59:45.591 --> 00:59:48.385
You know, Bala and I,
you know, she's a princess,

913
00:59:48.471 --> 00:59:51.668
and I'm a soil-relocation engineer.

914
00:59:51.752 --> 00:59:53.301
So wha... You're no... Whew!

915
00:59:53.791 --> 00:59:55.069
On the other hand, uh...

916
00:59:56.471 --> 00:59:57.781
I've gotta go back for her.

917
00:59:58.271 --> 01:00:00.268
I'll... I'll give you a lift!

918
01:00:00.830 --> 01:00:03.940
S- S-S... Whoa! Oh!

919
01:00:04.030 --> 01:00:06.104
It's the least I can do.

920
01:00:06.870 --> 01:00:12.108
Besides,
it's what my waddly-kittles would want.

921
01:00:14.470 --> 01:00:17.624
Uh, look,
how about a cup of joe first?

922
01:00:17.709 --> 01:00:20.864
- Well, old boy, saddle up.
- I saw a puddle of coffee over there.

923
01:00:20.950 --> 01:00:23.384
It... It... Whoa!

924
01:00:29.549 --> 01:00:30.586
Look out!

925
01:00:32.829 --> 01:00:34.106
Wait for my signal.

926
01:00:34.189 --> 01:00:35.945
Ah, Princess!

927
01:00:36.029 --> 01:00:38.747
- You're just in time.
- Take your hands off me.

928
01:00:39.628 --> 01:00:42.346
General, what exactly is going on here?

929
01:00:42.428 --> 01:00:45.986
- I demand an explanation.
- I'll explain everything afterwards.

930
01:00:46.548 --> 01:00:48.313
- Is the southeast entrance secure?
- Yes, sir.

931
01:00:48.748 --> 01:00:50.221
Not afterwards.

932
01:00:50.588 --> 01:00:51.547
Now.

933
01:00:54.707 --> 01:00:56.224
I don't like the way you think,

934
01:00:56.308 --> 01:00:58.697
and I don't like the way
you run this colony.

935
01:00:58.948 --> 01:01:01.741
And I don't like you. The wedding is off.

936
01:01:02.027 --> 01:01:04.177
Things are going to change around here.

937
01:01:04.747 --> 01:01:05.937
You're right, Princess.

938
01:01:06.707 --> 01:01:08.060
Things are going to change.

939
01:01:08.467 --> 01:01:10.180
Why don't we make her more comfortable?

940
01:01:10.267 --> 01:01:12.100
She'll be here for a while.

941
01:01:13.946 --> 01:01:15.376
What do you think you're doing?

942
01:01:15.746 --> 01:01:17.864
My mother will have your head!

943
01:01:17.946 --> 01:01:19.857
I doubt that.

944
01:01:20.826 --> 01:01:22.976
Ah, you've got a fighter's spirit, Bala.

945
01:01:23.066 --> 01:01:25.740
And that's just what we need
to start our new colony.

946
01:01:26.186 --> 01:01:28.816
We will rinse away all
the filth from our gutters.

947
01:01:28.906 --> 01:01:32.343
We'll start anew,
with you by my side as my queen.

948
01:01:33.185 --> 01:01:34.419
You're crazy.

949
01:01:36.705 --> 01:01:38.822
I believe history will see
things differently.

950
01:01:40.105 --> 01:01:42.342
All right, gentlemen.
Time to take your positions.

951
01:01:43.065 --> 01:01:45.935
Someday... Someday you'll thank me.

952
01:01:54.664 --> 01:01:57.021
Pull up! Pull up! Ah!

953
01:01:57.864 --> 01:01:59.862
There it is!

954
01:02:03.184 --> 01:02:06.457
Well, then, go get the woman you love, Z.

955
01:02:07.703 --> 01:02:09.657
So long, Chip. And thanks.

956
01:02:15.023 --> 01:02:15.982
You there!

957
01:02:16.063 --> 01:02:17.290
Where do you think you're goin'?

958
01:02:17.343 --> 01:02:20.136
Me? Oh, no, I was just... You know, I...

959
01:02:20.223 --> 01:02:21.773
You're not supposed to be out here.

960
01:02:22.222 --> 01:02:25.212
All workers are to report
to the tunnel-opening ceremonies.

961
01:02:25.303 --> 01:02:28.380
Oh! Yes, yes, of course!
The-The tunnel-opening ceremonies.

962
01:02:28.462 --> 01:02:31.617
I... Well, I should get going, then.
I...

963
01:02:31.702 --> 01:02:32.772
You know, the...

964
01:02:33.861 --> 01:02:34.658
Hey!

965
01:02:34.742 --> 01:02:37.776
I'm going to the...
the tunnel opening ceremonies.

966
01:02:37.861 --> 01:02:39.772
- I'd better get goin'.
- Get moving.

967
01:02:40.262 --> 01:02:42.652
I'm going to the...
the tunnel-opening ceremonies.

968
01:02:44.981 --> 01:02:47.458
Excuse me, please.
Tunnel-opening ceremonies.

969
01:02:47.541 --> 01:02:50.138
- Hey, worker!
- Opening the tunnel. They need me.

970
01:02:50.221 --> 01:02:52.371
- I'm the key man.
- Where do you think you're going?

971
01:02:52.461 --> 01:02:54.055
Tunnel-opening ceremonies.

972
01:02:58.101 --> 01:03:00.894
Hey, come on! Let me outta here!

973
01:03:00.981 --> 01:03:01.940
Hey!

974
01:03:08.980 --> 01:03:11.937
Gosh, this day just keeps getting
better and better.

975
01:03:12.980 --> 01:03:14.933
Big trouble!

976
01:03:16.019 --> 01:03:19.773
Are you listening to me out there?
I'm a princess,

977
01:03:19.859 --> 01:03:20.929
damn it!

978
01:03:25.299 --> 01:03:27.296
Wow, your manners haven't improved much.

979
01:03:27.379 --> 01:03:28.132
Z!

980
01:03:28.178 --> 01:03:30.089
Whoa! Whoa!

981
01:03:30.179 --> 01:03:34.053
- Oh!
- It's you. You came back for me.

982
01:03:34.139 --> 01:03:38.733
Well, yeah, I came back for you.
You know, I have strong feelings for you.

983
01:03:39.058 --> 01:03:42.048
Let's face it, you're... you're...
you're beautiful. I...

984
01:03:42.738 --> 01:03:46.688
A little combative at times,
but I think we can work on that.

985
01:03:46.778 --> 01:03:48.175
You talk too much.

986
01:03:51.097 --> 01:03:54.972
Gee, I think I'm about to become
the strong, silent type.

987
01:03:56.657 --> 01:04:00.215
Come on. The city's deserted.
We'd better get outta here.

988
01:04:00.297 --> 01:04:03.374
Z... we can't go.

989
01:04:03.457 --> 01:04:06.970
Mandible's insane.
He keeps talking about

990
01:04:07.057 --> 01:04:10.887
washing away the filth
and changing history and...

991
01:04:11.217 --> 01:04:13.334
and I think he's going to try
to kill my mother.

992
01:04:13.896 --> 01:04:16.690
Not just your mother, everyone.

993
01:04:17.016 --> 01:04:18.893
- What's going on?
- Look.

994
01:04:19.536 --> 01:04:20.933
Here we are, safe in the city.

995
01:04:21.655 --> 01:04:23.727
But they're gonna seal
everybody off in the MegaTunnel.

996
01:04:24.135 --> 01:04:26.329
And... here's the lake.

997
01:04:27.055 --> 01:04:28.169
You're right.

998
01:04:28.815 --> 01:04:30.288
We can't leave now.

999
01:04:31.615 --> 01:04:33.133
Come on. We gotta get down there.

1000
01:04:34.095 --> 01:04:37.085
Today is the realization of a dream.

1001
01:04:37.815 --> 01:04:39.452
A dream of a proud colony.

1002
01:04:40.174 --> 01:04:44.049
A pure colony. A colony reborn.

1003
01:04:48.334 --> 01:04:51.325
Moments from now this tunnel will open.

1004
01:04:51.814 --> 01:04:56.092
The past will be washed away,
and a new day will dawn.

1005
01:04:58.413 --> 01:05:00.007
A stirring speech, General.

1006
01:05:00.814 --> 01:05:03.051
I only wish my daughter
were here to appreciate it.

1007
01:05:03.133 --> 01:05:05.971
Your Majesty, I know how concerned
you are about Bala.

1008
01:05:06.453 --> 01:05:09.608
But my scouts are on her trail
and it's only a matter of time before...

1009
01:05:09.693 --> 01:05:12.606
General, I don't want to discuss it.
Just find her.

1010
01:05:13.333 --> 01:05:14.403
I will, Your Highness.

1011
01:05:15.893 --> 01:05:16.852
Goodbye.

1012
01:05:32.812 --> 01:05:34.122
Seal up the doors.

1013
01:05:35.132 --> 01:05:36.322
Cutter, did you hear me?

1014
01:05:36.811 --> 01:05:38.841
Sir, I've been thinking.

1015
01:05:39.691 --> 01:05:41.285
Do we need to go through with this?

1016
01:05:41.371 --> 01:05:43.848
Look at what these workers have done.

1017
01:05:43.931 --> 01:05:47.684
They got the right stuff.
Isn't there any other way?

1018
01:05:47.770 --> 01:05:49.364
Cutter, you're a fine officer.

1019
01:05:49.451 --> 01:05:52.081
You have discipline, courage, ability.

1020
01:05:52.811 --> 01:05:56.281
But you seem to have a certain weakness
for the lower orders I find disturbing.

1021
01:05:57.130 --> 01:06:00.884
- Now, are you with me?
- Sir, uh... I apologize.

1022
01:06:00.970 --> 01:06:04.080
- All right, then. Seal it up.
- Yes, sir.

1023
01:06:16.489 --> 01:06:18.846
As I look out
on this magnificent tunnel,

1024
01:06:19.809 --> 01:06:21.359
I am filled with pride.

1025
01:06:22.209 --> 01:06:24.718
- Jump!
- In these difficult times,

1026
01:06:24.808 --> 01:06:28.399
it is a great solace to know
that you, our workers...

1027
01:06:28.928 --> 01:06:30.578
Mom! Wait!

1028
01:06:30.769 --> 01:06:32.482
Every worker in the colony is here.

1029
01:06:33.488 --> 01:06:35.099
Hey, wait a minute.
That guy owes me money.

1030
01:06:35.168 --> 01:06:37.645
This tremendous accomplishment
is a testimony to the strength...

1031
01:06:37.728 --> 01:06:40.402
- People! Put your backs into it!
- Go warn your mother.

1032
01:06:40.488 --> 01:06:42.878
I gotta get to those diggers
before they break through!

1033
01:06:42.968 --> 01:06:44.125
There's not enough time!

1034
01:06:44.208 --> 01:06:46.838
Hey, leave the pessimism to me, okay?

1035
01:06:47.688 --> 01:06:51.202
Ow! Ooh! Yeeow!

1036
01:06:51.287 --> 01:06:53.764
Excuse me! Sorry about that. Excuse me.

1037
01:06:53.847 --> 01:06:56.957
In a few moments when our expert diggers
break through to the surface...

1038
01:06:57.047 --> 01:06:59.481
- Mom! Mom, stop.
- ...the sun will pour into this...

1039
01:07:00.007 --> 01:07:02.321
Bala! Where've you been?
Are you all right?

1040
01:07:02.406 --> 01:07:05.124
- I'm fine.
- What happened?

1041
01:07:05.487 --> 01:07:07.517
Mother, we're in terrible danger.

1042
01:07:18.646 --> 01:07:20.676
Put your backs into it, people.

1043
01:07:21.246 --> 01:07:23.876
Wait! Hold... Hey, stop digging!

1044
01:07:23.965 --> 01:07:26.596
- Z? Is that you?
- Weaver, stop!

1045
01:07:26.685 --> 01:07:28.878
Z! You're back!

1046
01:07:28.966 --> 01:07:30.635
- Oh, Z! Oh.
- Weaver!

1047
01:07:30.725 --> 01:07:33.279
Z! What's the matter?

1048
01:07:34.125 --> 01:07:37.115
Ho-Hold up, everyone! Stop! Stop digging!

1049
01:07:37.204 --> 01:07:39.758
- On whose authority?
- On your own authority.

1050
01:07:39.844 --> 01:07:41.962
If you break through that wall,
we're all gonna...

1051
01:07:42.044 --> 01:07:44.358
Drown! This tunnel is going to flood.

1052
01:07:44.445 --> 01:07:46.595
So we've got to get everyone out of here.

1053
01:07:48.644 --> 01:07:52.202
Look, I got orders,
and those orders say "dig."

1054
01:07:52.283 --> 01:07:54.957
What if someone ordered you
to jump off a bridge? Ju-Ju-Ju...

1055
01:07:55.763 --> 01:08:00.074
Brother, I'm asking the wrong guy here.
Look, think for yourselves!

1056
01:08:00.843 --> 01:08:02.917
Gimme that! I've had enough out of you.

1057
01:08:03.643 --> 01:08:04.602
Get back to work!

1058
01:08:05.483 --> 01:08:06.518
What's that noise?

1059
01:08:08.123 --> 01:08:09.082
Uh-oh.

1060
01:08:10.563 --> 01:08:12.080
- Let's get outta here!
- Run!

1061
01:08:14.163 --> 01:08:16.477
Run! Run! Keep going!

1062
01:08:17.083 --> 01:08:20.760
Everyone, listen to me.
We've all been deceived.

1063
01:08:22.082 --> 01:08:24.712
We need to calmly head toward the exits.

1064
01:08:24.802 --> 01:08:28.195
- Run for your lives! It's gonna flood!
- No. Don't panic.

1065
01:08:28.282 --> 01:08:31.436
- Don't panic!
- Every ant for himself!

1066
01:08:40.481 --> 01:08:42.554
- All the exits are blocked!
- We're trapped!

1067
01:09:06.359 --> 01:09:08.629
- What are we going to do?
- There's nothing we can do!

1068
01:09:15.359 --> 01:09:17.913
Yes, there is. Weaver, give me a leg up!

1069
01:09:18.958 --> 01:09:21.152
Everyone, listen to me!

1070
01:09:21.239 --> 01:09:23.716
- Who the heck are you?
- He's Z!

1071
01:09:27.159 --> 01:09:31.109
Listen, we gotta help each other
get outta here before we all drown!

1072
01:09:31.198 --> 01:09:31.995
How?

1073
01:09:32.078 --> 01:09:34.271
- By making a ladder.
- A ladder!

1074
01:09:34.358 --> 01:09:37.228
Hey, if we built this, we can do anything.

1075
01:09:37.558 --> 01:09:41.072
- Okay, let's move it!
- I'm on it. All of you, gather round.

1076
01:09:41.158 --> 01:09:42.391
You, start climbing.

1077
01:09:43.517 --> 01:09:46.791
- Grab my arm.
- All right. Here I go.

1078
01:09:46.877 --> 01:09:48.547
- Go, go, go!
- All right!

1079
01:09:50.837 --> 01:09:52.474
Excuse me, Your Majesty.

1080
01:09:54.717 --> 01:09:57.074
Z, I've gotta help my mom.

1081
01:09:57.677 --> 01:09:58.473
Don't worry.

1082
01:09:58.557 --> 01:10:00.630
I know almost exactly what I'm doing.

1083
01:10:03.357 --> 01:10:04.514
I'll see you at the top.

1084
01:10:08.756 --> 01:10:14.114
Gentlemen, there comes a time
in the evolution of a perfect colony

1085
01:10:14.395 --> 01:10:17.550
when the strong are meant
to rise above the weak.

1086
01:10:18.876 --> 01:10:21.026
Now is that time.

1087
01:10:21.915 --> 01:10:26.226
<i>Below us right now,
the weak elements of the colony</i>

1088
01:10:26.315 --> 01:10:27.625
<i>are being washed away.</i>

1089
01:10:29.195 --> 01:10:33.025
Oh, my God, we're not gonna make it!

1090
01:10:33.115 --> 01:10:35.908
- We need more ants.
- You two better get up there.

1091
01:10:35.995 --> 01:10:38.232
Weaver, you can't hold it alone.

1092
01:10:38.315 --> 01:10:39.864
Get going!

1093
01:10:40.834 --> 01:10:41.904
Hang in there, buddy.

1094
01:10:56.314 --> 01:10:58.791
- Got it!
- Hurry up! Go, go, go, go!

1095
01:11:02.393 --> 01:11:06.310
Our princess is secured,
and our glorious future is at hand.

1096
01:11:06.912 --> 01:11:08.462
We can all stand proud.

1097
01:11:08.913 --> 01:11:11.423
It is time for a new beginning.

1098
01:11:21.592 --> 01:11:24.626
What the hell is that?

1099
01:11:25.112 --> 01:11:27.022
I think that's the weak elements, sir.

1100
01:11:27.112 --> 01:11:30.505
- Gimme a hand!
- Z! You?

1101
01:11:31.191 --> 01:11:35.502
Let go! Don't you understand?
It's for the good of the colony.

1102
01:11:35.591 --> 01:11:38.668
What are you saying? We are the colony!

1103
01:11:42.631 --> 01:11:43.590
Cutter!

1104
01:11:44.271 --> 01:11:45.024
What are you doing?

1105
01:11:45.111 --> 01:11:48.068
Something I should've done
a long time ago.

1106
01:11:48.510 --> 01:11:51.424
This is for the good of the colony, sir.

1107
01:11:53.350 --> 01:11:55.424
You useless, ungrateful maggot!

1108
01:11:55.510 --> 01:11:58.260
- I am the colony!
- Look out!

1109
01:11:58.350 --> 01:12:02.060
Oof! Ah!

1110
01:12:09.069 --> 01:12:10.028
Z!

1111
01:12:11.429 --> 01:12:14.626
Men, let's move it!
Get these ants up here.

1112
01:12:18.468 --> 01:12:20.825
- Keep it moving.
- Thank goodness we made it.

1113
01:12:26.468 --> 01:12:27.427
Wait here.

1114
01:12:36.427 --> 01:12:38.425
- Uh! Okay.
- Thank you. Ooh!

1115
01:12:38.708 --> 01:12:39.667
Weaver!

1116
01:12:41.147 --> 01:12:42.217
Where's Z?

1117
01:12:50.587 --> 01:12:51.546
Oh, no.

1118
01:12:52.467 --> 01:12:54.377
Back up, everybody, back up!

1119
01:12:54.467 --> 01:12:58.057
- Give him some air. Back up!
- Z, oh, Z.

1120
01:13:02.506 --> 01:13:03.816
Please wake up.

1121
01:13:06.185 --> 01:13:07.299
Oh, no!

1122
01:13:12.426 --> 01:13:15.176
Huh!

1123
01:13:22.145 --> 01:13:23.182
Yowch!

1124
01:13:24.745 --> 01:13:27.899
You know, Weaver,
you still owe me that dinner.

1125
01:13:29.264 --> 01:13:30.223
Baby love.

1126
01:13:31.505 --> 01:13:34.375
- We made it, Z!
- You da ant!

1127
01:13:35.144 --> 01:13:37.097
- Eh!
- You did it.

1128
01:13:37.544 --> 01:13:38.503
We did it.

1129
01:13:40.384 --> 01:13:42.021
- Fellas, fellas, please.
- Oh! Oh!

1130
01:13:42.104 --> 01:13:44.418
This is very embarrassing for me, I...

1131
01:13:44.504 --> 01:13:48.137
On the other hand,
I probably could get used to this.

1132
01:13:51.264 --> 01:13:53.653
<i>There you have it.
Your average "boy meets girl,</i>

1133
01:13:53.743 --> 01:13:57.661
<i>boy likes girl, boy changes
underlying social order" story.</i>

1134
01:13:58.703 --> 01:14:00.056
<i>So, what else can I tell you?</i>

1135
01:14:00.543 --> 01:14:03.140
<i>We rebuilt the colony.
It's even better than before,</i>

1136
01:14:03.223 --> 01:14:06.540
<i>you know, 'cause now it has
a very large indoor swimming pool.</i>

1137
01:14:07.023 --> 01:14:10.057
<i>Bala and I, incidentally,
are thinking of starting a family,</i>

1138
01:14:10.382 --> 01:14:14.496
<i>you know, just a few kids,
maybe a million or two to begin with.</i>

1139
01:14:14.822 --> 01:14:18.936
<i>And I'm workin' with a new therapist,
you know, terrific, absolutely terrific.</i>

1140
01:14:19.021 --> 01:14:22.099
<i>He's been putting me in touch
with my inner maggot,</i>

1141
01:14:22.181 --> 01:14:23.578
<i>which is helping me a great deal.</i>

1142
01:14:23.662 --> 01:14:26.936
<i>And, you know, I finally feel like
I've found my place.</i>

1143
01:14:27.021 --> 01:14:29.259
<i>And you know what?
It's right back where I started.</i>

1144
01:14:29.741 --> 01:14:33.015
<i>But the difference is,
this time I chose it.</i>

1145
01:14:38.421 --> 01:14:41.214
<i>♪ Just what makes that little old ant ♪</i>

1146
01:14:41.301 --> 01:14:44.335
<i>♪ Think he'll move
That rubber-tree plant ♪</i>

1147
01:14:44.420 --> 01:14:49.418
<i>♪ Anyone knows an ant can't
Move a rubber-tree plant ♪</i>

1148
01:14:49.500 --> 01:14:52.850
<i>♪ But he's got high hopes ♪</i>

1149
01:14:52.940 --> 01:14:55.897
<i>♪ He's got high hopes ♪</i>

1150
01:14:55.980 --> 01:14:59.090
<i>♪ He's got high apple pie ♪</i>

1151
01:14:59.180 --> 01:15:01.657
<i>♪ In the sky hopes ♪</i>

1152
01:15:01.739 --> 01:15:04.293
<i>♪ So anytime you're gettin' low ♪</i>

1153
01:15:04.380 --> 01:15:08.297
<i>♪ 'Stead of lettin' go
Just remember that ant ♪</i>

1154
01:15:08.899 --> 01:15:18.376
<i>♪ Oops, there goes another
Rubber-tree plant ♪</i>

1155
01:15:21.058 --> 01:15:23.972
<i>♪ Once there was a silly old ram ♪</i>

1156
01:15:24.058 --> 01:15:26.896
<i>♪ Thought he'd punch a hole in a dam ♪</i>

1157
01:15:26.978 --> 01:15:30.175
<i>♪ No one could make that ram scram ♪</i>

1158
01:15:30.258 --> 01:15:35.212
<i>♪ He kept buttin' that dam
'Cause he had high hopes ♪</i>

1159
01:15:35.297 --> 01:15:38.135
<i>♪ He had high hopes ♪</i>

1160
01:15:38.217 --> 01:15:41.252
<i>♪ He had high apple pie ♪</i>

1161
01:15:41.337 --> 01:15:43.814
<i>♪ In the sky hopes ♪</i>

1162
01:15:43.896 --> 01:15:48.011
<i>♪ So anytime you're feelin' bad
'Stead of feelin' sad ♪</i>

1163
01:15:48.097 --> 01:15:50.214
<i>♪ Just remember that ram ♪</i>

1164
01:15:51.056 --> 01:16:00.293
<i>♪ Oops, there goes
A billion-kilowatt dam ♪</i>

1165
01:16:01.776 --> 01:16:05.093
<i>♪ So keep your high hopes ♪</i>

1166
01:16:05.175 --> 01:16:08.089
<i>♪ Keep your high hopes ♪</i>

1167
01:16:08.175 --> 01:16:11.209
<i>♪ Keep those high apple pie ♪</i>

1168
01:16:11.296 --> 01:16:13.805
<i>♪ In the sky hopes ♪</i>

1169
01:16:13.895 --> 01:16:16.165
<i>♪ A problem's just a toy balloon ♪</i>

1170
01:16:16.255 --> 01:16:19.845
<i>♪ They'll be bursting soon
They're just bound to go pop ♪</i>

1171
01:16:21.095 --> 01:16:30.368
<i>♪ Oops, there goes another problem
Ker-plop ♪</i>

1172
01:16:31.934 --> 01:16:32.928
<i>♪ Ker-plop! ♪</i>

